// Strings in English GoniometroScreen Perform Goniometry Restart Goniometry Quadrant Direct Angle Opposite Angle Supplementary Angle Opposite Supplementary Instructions Close Patients Import Photo Capture Photo Help Logout Exit Angle found: %1$s° --° Tip 1: Choose between \"Import Photo\" or \"Take Photo\". Tip 2: Remember to choose a photo that is facing the joint to be measured, to avoid possible errors and increase goniometry accuracy. Tip 3: Click on \"Perform Goniometry\". Tip 4: Position your finger where the joint \"Axis\" would be located, then drag it towards the \"Fixed Arm of the goniometer\" reference. Tip 5: After that, click on the reference position of the \"Moving Arm of the goniometer\". Tip 6: This will give you the angle formed between the two arms of the Goniometer. Tip 7: You can change the angle reference in \"Change Quadrant\", depending on the plane and joint being measured. Tip 8: If the goniometry was not done correctly, you can click on \"Restart Goniometry\" to try again. Tip 9: You can save your results in the \"Goniometry\" option (This feature is still under development and improvements will be made in the future). Tip 10: The app\'s goniometer uses a real goniometer as a reference, including its arms, axis, and quadrants. Tip 11: It is recommended to use \"Book: Fundamentals of Musculoskeletal Assessment Techniques by Marcia E. Epler, M. Lynn Palmer\" as a reference for any goniometry performed, both in the app and with a physical goniometer. Note: The app is not intended to replace the physical goniometer, but rather serve as an alternative tool for physiotherapists. Therefore, it may present inaccuracies in this initial stage of development, and all feedback will be welcome to improve its operation.
